Regardie, Israel - The Complete Golden Dawn 6th Ed., 2002, 717 pages

This book is truly the fountainhead of occult wisdom in this age, and is considered by many to be the book that started the modern occult movement. The book is divided into several basic sections. First are the knowledge lectures, where you will learn the basics of the Qabalah, symbolism, meditation, geomancy and more. This is followed by the rituals of the Outer Order, the rituals of the Inner Order, the basic rituals of magic and the construction, consecration, and means of using the magical tools. Once you have these you can go on to evocation rituals, talismans, and invocations. A 'must read' for every student of the occult.


